<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-06T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9935</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-06T12:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1918—noon.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5517. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 291. Embassy’s 4892, August 27, 6 p.m., your 372.<note n="3" xml:id="d175fn3">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1041">p.
                                        1041</ref>.</note> War Trade Board’s position in matter in
                                question entirely set forth in Department’s No. 5506, our 287,
                                September 4, 3 p.m. To make definite War Trade Board’s position
                                reference scope of conference <pb facs="0222" n="1056" xml:id="pg_1056"/> activities, as intended and considered
                                desirable by War Trade Board and by Washington representatives of
                                French, English, Italian Governments, conference will consider all
                                cases where normal action of Government concerned would be
                                restriction of transaction owing to enemy character or affiliation
                                of a person involved therein.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>